<hr size=1> True, perception comes from a lot of places, but one guaranteed source of that perception is an inability to keep up with the group, especially at low levels.  The wizard sees it, the group sees it (from constant &quot;LoM/OOM&quot; calls from the wizard).  And you're right, a lot of it has to do with twinking, but even if you took a completely new group of characters and leveled them up together, the wizard would still be behind the rest of the group until they hit their 50s.  <br>
<br>
The melee weapons and armour available in the bazaar and simply the improved stuff that drops in newer zones improves a low level melee toon more than a low level wizard (oddly, it benefits a low level cleric too, as they have to heal the melees less).  What we need is a compensating increase in efficiency at lower levels, either through better mana regen (unlikely) or spells with better ratios.  Extending the spear line would address this without being imbalancing nor creating a new &quot;artificial&quot; line of compensating spells.  Adding Raystonn's melee-range requirement to them would actually be an interesting twist.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm derailing here with &quot;the plight of the low-level wizard&quot; (which has been heard a million times before - I know), but I really do think it's one of the major contributing factors to how other classes perceive us. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1271<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 3:28:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26268.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> I really do think that KEI is the natural counter to that though.<br>
